  <h3>Introduction to HTML</h3>

  <ul>
    <li> HTML tags surrounded by angle brackets: <code>&lt></code> <br>
    <li> <code>&lth1>, ..., &lth6></code> tags = headers, large to small. End tags needed. <br>
    <li> <code>&ltbr></code> tag = line break, does not use end tag
    <li> <code>&ltcenter></code> tag centers content. End tag rqd.
    <li> <code>&ltem></code> and <code>&lti></code> are 'emphasis' and 'italics' respectively. Both look like italic font. <code>&ltem></code> preferable in most situations.
    <li> <code>&ltstrong></code> and <code>&ltb></code> both make font bold, but strong confers meaning, so it is preferred.
    <li> <code>&ltol></code> and <code>&ltul></code> are ordered and unordered lists respectively. <code>&ltli></code> used for each item.
    <li> <code>&ltimg src="<i>source</i>" alt="<i>text displayed if image not present</i>"></code> for images.
    <li> <code>&lta href="https://..."><em>Link Text</em>&lt/a></code> for hyperlinks
  </ul>

